                            <comment id="15702246" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2016 15:36:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user zentol opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2887&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2887&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4870&quot; title=&quot;ContinuousFileMonitoringFunction does not properly handle absolut Windows paths&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4870&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4870&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5162&quot; title=&quot;BlobRecoveryItCase#testBlobServerRecovery fails on Windows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5162&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5162&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Fix issues on windows related to Path/URI generation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This PR fixes the FileSystemBlocStore and ContinuousFileMonitoringFunction on Windows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    In both classes an URI is generated from a String and given to a Flink FileSystem instance. However, on Windows it is a hard requirement that all URI&apos;s that are generated first go through the Path class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/zentol/flink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/zentol/flink&lt;/a&gt; 5160_4870_test_uri_generation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2887.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2887.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

